FAQs
Is a degree from Canada recognized internationally?
Yes, degrees from Canadian universities are recognized and respected worldwide, enhancing your career prospects globally.

What is the cost of study in Canada?
Tuition fees range from CAD 20,000 to CAD 40,000 per year for undergraduate programs, with living expenses ranging from CAD 10,000 to CAD 15,000 per year.

Are there scholarships available for international students in Canada?

Yes, numerous scholarships are available from universities, the Canadian government, and private organizations based on academic merit and financial need.

How can Qadri International assist with study in Canada?
Qadri International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, and visa guidance to ensure a successful study abroad experience.

What is the Post-Graduation Work Permit (PGWP) in Canada?
The PGWP allows graduates to work in Canada for up to three years after completing their studies, providing valuable work experience and a pathway to permanent residency.
